title: Led Zeppelin - 1975.05.24 Earl's Court, London
description:
Led Zeppelin - 1975.05.24 Earl's Court, London   

Led Zeppelin 1975-05-24 soundboard He Must Be Dazed And Confused
Earl's Court, London, England
EVSD Box Set "Earl's Court The Final Option"

Led Zeppelin
Earl's Court
London, England
May 24, 1975

Source: 
Excellent soundboard recording. 

Details: 
The recording is a very well balanced professional video soundtrack. 

Audience source to fill gaps:
Very good to excellent 1st audience recording. A clear and dynamic 
source with nice spectrum. Taped much close to the stage.

Tracklist:

102 rock and roll
103 sick again
104 over the hills and far away

106 the song remains the same
107 the rain song
108 kashmir

402 audience
403 whole lotta love
404 black dog
405 after show

Comments: 
This is a monster of a show. The best of the five Earl's Court gigs, this show 
has the band reaching a peak for 1975, one that is even better than Seattle and 
LA two months earlier. Nicky Horne simply introduced the band: "Welcome to Earl's Court. For the next three hours ... your mother wouldn't like it!" No Quarter must be the best version ever recorded, and Dazed And Confused is an incredible journey. Dennis Healey was again remembered during the introduction to the Dazed: "We gotta fly soon. Y'know how it goes with Dennis ... dear Dennis. Private enterprise ... no artists in the country anymore ... he must be dazed and confused!" Stairway To Heaven contains probably the best solo ever by Jimmy on the song while Plant's vocal is not the best. The humour was belonged to the whole group so Bonham took the microphone as they climbed for the encores and said: "I'd like to say at this point that I think football's a load of bollocks!" what caued a quick retort from Plant: "I'd like to say that soccer's a wonderful sport, the best sport."
